# iterations/07-multi-gpu-mvp/config-jd-dc.env
# DC host config for jd_reparse
#
# Why a separate config:
#   jd_reparse is excluded from non-DC fleet scaling. Non-DC hosts running
#   sustained multi-GPU inference crash at 5–11 min under full load
#   (4x RTX 3090 @ ~1400W total → host power/thermal collapse at 5m;
#    1x RTX PRO 6000 WS @ ~600W → collapse at ~11m). jd_reparse's long
#   per-record latency (multi-slice, ~162s/record avg) keeps GPUs pinned at
#   100% for longer continuous stretches than job_skills or company_enrich,
#   making it the task most likely to expose host instability.
#
# Design choices:
#   - REQUIRE_DATACENTER=true: proper power delivery + cooling for sustained load
#   - NUM_GPUS=4: fallback path [4, 2] handles availability gaps gracefully.
#     2x DC offer is still viable: (VRAM-6)/0.5 × 2 = ~72 workers minimum.
#   - No GPU_NAME filter: open to full RTX family; DC supply is thinner so
#     name-filtering would unnecessarily narrow available offers.
#   - MAX_PRICE=0.80: DC offers run higher than non-DC. 4x DC may reach $0.80;
#     2x DC typically $0.30–0.50. Fallback absorbs the price difference.
#   - MIN_TFLOPS_PER_GPU=25: same floor as config-4x.env — ensures ≥100 TFLOPS
#     total across a 4-card fleet, ≥50 across a 2-card fallback.
#   - MIN_VRAM_GB=16: minimum for useful slot count.
#     Formula: (16-6)/0.5 = 20 slots/GPU. At 2x: 40 workers; at 4x: 80 workers.
#   - MAX_VRAM_GB=36: caps at 5090/3090/A5000 tier; excludes high-VRAM outliers.

# --- Offer selection ---
LLM_VAST_NUM_GPUS=4
LLM_VAST_GPU_NAME=
LLM_VAST_MAX_PRICE=0.80
LLM_VAST_MIN_VRAM_GB=16
LLM_VAST_MAX_VRAM_GB=36
LLM_VAST_MIN_TFLOPS_PER_GPU=25
LLM_VAST_MIN_INET_DOWN_MBPS=800
LLM_VAST_REQUIRE_DATACENTER=true
LLM_VAST_REQUIRE_VERIFIED=true
LLM_VAST_MAX_BW_COST_USD=0.09
